In Terraform v0.15+, terraform taint is removed. Instead, use:

terraform apply -replace="aws_instance.my"

What it does:

forces a specific resource to be destroyed and recreated even if no config change

When to use:

EC2 is unhealthy/corrupted    → force recreate
Resource stuck in bad state   → force recreate

Old vs New:

terraform taint aws_instance.my   → deprecated ❌
terraform apply -replace="aws_instance.my"  → current way ✅
